The President criticizes Senate Republicans for choosing to raise taxes on hardworking Americans instead of asking the wealthy to pay their fair share. He argues that it is unacceptable to raise taxes on the middle class when they are still recovering from economic difficulties. The President emphasizes the need to prioritize the economy and the security of the middle class and urges Congress to work together for the benefit of the American people. He calls on Congress to stop playing politics and take action to protect American families and small business owners.